SUMMARY:Summer 2026 Workshop Series: The Honest Scholar: Best Practices in 
 the Ethical Conduct of Research
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ["Provost's Office"\, 'Beyond The Classroom'\, 'D
 ivision of Student Affairs']\\nCategory: Lecture/Panel Discussion\\nTuesda
 ys and Thursdays in Sci 101 from 12-1:30pm. Lunch will be provided. Studen
 ts will learn the basic rules for ethical conduct of research\, and the th
 ree (3) things that constitute research misconduct. Think Plagiarism! We'l
 l consider responsible conduct of research (RCR) principles and how they a
 pply to your scholarly activities\, and research of all kinds\, whether in
  the lab\, the archive\, or the field. Presented by Jena Fioravanti\, Dire
 ctor of the Office of Research Integrity and Engagement.\\nDetails: https:
 //swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1395671
 874
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1395671874
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Panel Discussion
END:VEVENT
